 {"id":"asupersync-5jm","title":"[fastapi-integration] 1.2: TcpStream Trait Definition","description":"# 1.2: TcpStream Trait Definition

## Objective
Define the TcpStream trait for reading/writing data over TCP connections.

## Background

### Design Goals
1. **AsyncRead/AsyncWrite compatible**: Works with existing async ecosystem patterns
2. **Split support**: Independent read/write halves for concurrent I/O
3. **Budget-aware**: I/O timeouts via budget
4. **Two-phase semantics**: For cancel-correct I/O operations

## Requirements

### 1. Core Trait Definition
```rust
/// A TCP stream for bidirectional communication.
///
/// Implements [`AsyncRead`] and [`AsyncWrite`] for compatibility
/// with standard async patterns. All I/O operations respect the
/// budget in the capability context.
///
/// # Cancel-Correctness
/// Read and write operations use two-phase semantics:
/// 1. Submit: I/O is submitted to the kernel
/// 2. Complete: I/O completes or is cancelled
///
/// If cancelled between submit and complete:
/// - Read: No data loss (data still in kernel buffer)
/// - Write: Partial write may have occurred (check bytes_written)
///
/// # Example
/// ```rust
/// async fn echo(cx: &Cx<'_>, stream: TcpStream) -> Outcome<(), IoError> {
///     let mut buf = [0u8; 1024];
///     loop {
///         let n = stream.read(cx, &mut buf).await?;
///         if n == 0 { break; }
///         stream.write_all(cx, &buf[..n]).await?;
///     }
///     Ok(())
/// }
/// ```
pub trait TcpStream: AsyncRead + AsyncWrite + Sized {
    /// Connect to a remote address.
    ///
    /// # Budget
    /// Connection timeout respects `cx.remaining_budget().deadline`.
    async fn connect(cx: &Cx<'_>, addr: impl ToSocketAddrs) -> Outcome<Self, IoError>;

    /// Read data into buffer, returning bytes read.
    ///
    /// Returns `Ok(0)` on EOF. Respects budget deadline.
    async fn read(&self, cx: &Cx<'_>, buf: &mut [u8]) -> Outcome<usize, IoError>;

    /// Read exactly `buf.len()` bytes.
    ///
    /// # Errors
    /// - `IoError::UnexpectedEof`: Connection closed before buffer filled
    async fn read_exact(&self, cx: &Cx<'_>, buf: &mut [u8]) -> Outcome<(), IoError>;

    /// Write data from buffer, returning bytes written.
    async fn write(&self, cx: &Cx<'_>, buf: &[u8]) -> Outcome<usize, IoError>;

    /// Write entire buffer.
    async fn write_all(&self, cx: &Cx<'_>, buf: &[u8]) -> Outcome<(), IoError>;

    /// Flush any buffered data to the kernel.
    async fn flush(&self, cx: &Cx<'_>) -> Outcome<(), IoError>;

    /// Split into independent read and write halves.
    ///
    /// Both halves can be used concurrently. The stream is
    /// reconstructed when both halves are dropped.
    fn split(self) -> (Self::ReadHalf, Self::WriteHalf);

    /// Shut down the write side of the connection.
    ///
    /// After shutdown, writes return `IoError::NotConnected`.
    /// Reads may still return data until the peer closes.
    async fn shutdown(&self, cx: &Cx<'_>) -> Outcome<(), IoError>;

    /// Return the remote socket address.
    fn peer_addr(&self) -> Outcome<SocketAddr, IoError>;

    /// Return the local socket address.
    fn local_addr(&self) -> Outcome<SocketAddr, IoError>;

    /// Set TCP_NODELAY (disable Nagle's algorithm).
    fn set_nodelay(&self, nodelay: bool) -> Outcome<(), IoError>;

    /// Get TCP_NODELAY setting.
    fn nodelay(&self) -> Outcome<bool, IoError>;

    /// Associated types for split halves
    type ReadHalf: AsyncRead;
    type WriteHalf: AsyncWrite;
}
```

### 2. Connection Builder
```rust
pub struct TcpStreamBuilder {
    addr: SocketAddr,
    connect_timeout: Option<Duration>,
    nodelay: bool,
    keepalive: Option<TcpKeepalive>,
    // ... platform-specific options
}

impl TcpStreamBuilder {
    pub fn new(addr: impl ToSocketAddrs) -> Self;
    pub fn connect_timeout(self, timeout: Duration) -> Self;
    pub fn nodelay(self, enable: bool) -> Self;
    pub fn keepalive(self, config: TcpKeepalive) -> Self;
    pub async fn connect(self, cx: &Cx<'_>) -> Outcome<impl TcpStream, IoError>;
}
```

### 3. Buffered Wrappers
```rust
/// Buffered reader for efficient small reads.
pub struct BufReader<S: TcpStream> {
    inner: S::ReadHalf,
    buffer: Vec<u8>,
    pos: usize,
    cap: usize,
}

impl<S: TcpStream> BufReader<S> {
    pub fn new(stream: S::ReadHalf) -> Self;
    pub fn with_capacity(stream: S::ReadHalf, capacity: usize) -> Self;

    /// Read until delimiter, returning the line including delimiter.
    pub async fn read_until(&mut self, cx: &Cx<'_>, delim: u8, buf: &mut Vec<u8>) 
        -> Outcome<usize, IoError>;

    /// Read a line (until \n).
    pub async fn read_line(&mut self, cx: &Cx<'_>, buf: &mut String) 
        -> Outcome<usize, IoError>;
}

/// Buffered writer for efficient small writes.
pub struct BufWriter<S: TcpStream> {
    inner: S::WriteHalf,
    buffer: Vec<u8>,
}
```

