 {"id":"asupersync-5ozjd","title":"Update cancellation propagation to build cause chains","description":"## Overview

Update the cancellation propagation logic to properly chain CancelReasons when cancelling child regions.

## Background

When a parent region cancels, all child regions must be cancelled with a CancelReason that links back to the parent's reason.

## Current Flow (simplified)

```rust
fn cancel_region(region_id: RegionId, reason: CancelReason) {
    // Mark region cancelled
    // For each child region:
    //   cancel_region(child_id, CancelReason::Parent)  // Loses information!
}
```

## Target Flow

```rust
fn cancel_region(region_id: RegionId, reason: CancelReason) {
    // Mark region cancelled with this reason
    self.regions[region_id].cancel_reason = Some(reason.clone());

    // For each child region, create chained reason
    for child_id in self.regions[region_id].children.clone() {
        let child_reason = CancelReason::new(CancelKind::ParentCancelled, region_id)
            .caused_by(reason.clone());
        cancel_region(child_id, child_reason);
    }
}
```

## Chain Example

Consider this region tree:
```
Root (region-0)
  └── Service (region-1)
        └── Request (region-2)
              └── DbQuery (region-3)
```

If Service times out (Deadline), the DbQuery's cancel chain should be:
```
DbQuery reason: ParentCancelled (region-2)
  └── cause: ParentCancelled (region-1)
        └── cause: Deadline (region-1)
```

## Places to Update

1. Region::cancel() - the explicit cancel API
2. Budget enforcement - when deadline/quota triggers cancel
3. Runtime shutdown - propagates Shutdown reason
4. Race combinators - RaceLost for losing branches

